FBIS4-4603 "dreas064_c_94012" FBIS-EAS-94-064 Daily Report 3 Apr 1994 North Korea Joint ROK-U.S. War Exercises Denounced Joint ROK-U.S. War Exercises Denounced Air Exercise on 1 Apr Noted SK0304083094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0817 GMT 3 Apr 94 SK0304083094 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, April 3 (KCNA) -- Formations of overseas-based pursuit-assault planes and VTOL [vertical takeoff and landing] assault planes of the U.S. Marines on April 1 launched surprise attack exercises on strategic objects in the northern half of Korea in the skies above Yongwol, Pyongchang, Oeyon islet and Chungju, South Korea, in coordination with flying corps of the U.S. Air Force in South Korea and the puppet Air Force, according to military sources. Meanwhile, tank groups and armed bandits of the puppet Army fired scores of tank guns and hundreds of large-calibre machine gun bullets in the area of Paju County. These show that the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean puppets are recklessly rushing ahead toward a war against the North.
